    Example Sound File

    coryphoda.Rd

    A single calling song of *Coryphoda albidicollis*, a Phaneropterinae from Central Chile.

    coryphoda

    Format

    An object of class Wave. The Wave object contains:

    left

    The left audio channel (if stereo).

    samp.rate

    The sampling rate in Hz.

    bit

    The bit depth (e.g., 16 for CD quality).

    duration

    The total duration of the sound file in seconds.

    Source

    Original recording by Francisco Rivas Fuenzalida.

    Details

    This sound was recorded at a sampling rate of 96 kHz. The ambient temperature was 22.6 degrees Celsius. The sound file has been imported into an R object using the readWave function from the tuneR package.

    Examples

    if (FALSE) { # \dontrun{
data(coryphoda)
summary(coryphoda)
spectrum_plotly(coryphoda)
} # }
